00:01:00.671 --> 00:01:02.838
you're going to produce X

00:01:02.838 --> 00:01:04.578
and then if you took that as your input

00:01:04.578 --> 00:01:06.995
into the square root function

00:01:08.162 --> 00:01:10.941
you are going to produce Y.

00:01:10.941 --> 00:01:14.811
So, you could just view this
as just one big box here,

00:01:14.811 --> 00:01:16.894
that Y is a function of Y

00:01:18.420 --> 00:01:21.459
but now let's actually
answer their question.

00:01:21.459 --> 00:01:24.637
To tackle it we just have
to apply the chain rule.

00:01:24.637 --> 00:01:28.316
The chain rule tells us
that the derivative of Y

00:01:28.316 --> 00:01:30.242
with respect to T

00:01:30.242 --> 00:01:33.054
is going to be equal
to the derivative of Y

00:01:33.054 --> 00:01:36.637
